# Privacy Policy

**Effective Date:** March 17, 2026

## 1. Introduction

Attendance Calculator ("the App") helps students calculate their current attendance percentage and determine how many classes they need to attend or can miss to maintain a desired attendance percentage.

This Privacy Policy explains how information is handled when you use the application.

---

## 2. Information Collected by the App

The application itself does not collect or store personal information such as name, email address, or phone number.

Any attendance data entered into the app (such as total classes, attended classes, or desired attendance percentage) is stored locally on the user's device and is not transmitted to any external server.

---

## 3. Advertising

The application uses **Google AdMob** to display advertisements.

AdMob may collect certain information automatically to provide and improve advertising services. This information may include:

* Device information
* Advertising ID
* IP address
* App interaction data
* Approximate location derived from IP address

This data collection is handled by Google according to their privacy policies.

More information can be found here:
https://policies.google.com/privacy

---

## 4. Third-Party Services

The app uses the following third-party service:

* Google AdMob (advertising)

These services may collect information as described in their own privacy policies.

---

## 5. Children's Privacy

This application is not directed toward children under the age of 13. The app does not knowingly collect personal information from children.

---

## 6. Data Security

Since the application does not store personal user information on external servers, user data entered into the app remains on the user's device.

---

## 7. Changes to This Privacy Policy

The Privacy Policy may be updated from time to time. Changes will be reflected on the page where this policy is hosted.

